  <!-- Choosing Section -->
  <section class="section bg-white" id="choosing">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">How to Choose the Right Dog Daycare Software</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8">
          The market has a wide range of options, from generic appointment scheduling tools adapted for pet care to purpose-built kennel management systems. The right choice depends on your service mix, team size, and how much of your current admin you want to automate. Here's what to look for — and what to avoid.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">What Matters Most</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-red font-bold flex-shrink-0">→</span>
            <span><strong>Purpose-built for pet care:</strong> Generic booking tools miss industry-specific features like vaccination tracking, playgroup management, and report cards. You'll spend time working around gaps rather than being supported by the tool.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-red font-bold flex-shrink-0">→</span>
            <span><strong>Real-time capacity at playgroup level:</strong> Total capacity limits are not enough. The system needs to enforce rules by group, weight class, or however you segment your facility.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-red font-bold flex-shrink-0">→</span>
            <span><strong>Vaccination tracking that sends reminders:</strong> Storing records is table stakes. What matters is automatic owner alerts and a compliance dashboard you can check in 30 seconds.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-red font-bold flex-shrink-0">→</span>
            <span><strong>Owner portal for self-service:</strong> Owners should be able to book, pay, upload vaccine records, and view report cards without contacting you. This is where the time savings really compound.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-red font-bold flex-shrink-0">→</span>
            <span><strong>Mobile-friendly for staff:</strong> Your team check dogs in and out from the front desk, not a desktop in an office. The interface needs to work on a tablet or phone in a busy environment.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-red font-bold flex-shrink-0">→</span>
            <span><strong>Flat pricing with no per-booking fees:</strong> Per-transaction pricing punishes growth. As your booking volume increases, the cost increases proportionally. Flat monthly pricing scales with you.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Red Flags</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-red-600 font-bold flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
            <span><strong>Per-booking transaction fees</strong> — 3–5% per booking adds up to thousands per year at typical daycare volumes</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-red-600 font-bold flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
            <span><strong>No vaccination tracking</strong> — any system that can't manage vaccine records will cost you compliance time daily</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-red-600 font-bold flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
            <span><strong>Desktop-only interfaces</strong> — staff need mobile access at the front desk and in the yard</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-red-600 font-bold flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
            <span><strong>No trial period</strong> — any reputable software provider will give you a free trial on real bookings before asking for payment</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-red-600 font-bold flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
            <span><strong>Built for spas or hair salons, adapted for pets</strong> — you'll find missing features and workarounds for basic pet care operations</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700">Related guides: <a href="/kennel-software/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline font-semibold">Kennel Software Guide</a> · <a href="/dog-boarding-software/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline font-semibold">Dog Boarding Software</a> · <a href="/cattery-software/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline font-semibold">Cattery Software</a></p>
